description: Retrieves details of events stored with Amazon Fraud Detector. This action does not retrieve prediction results.

parameters.name: eventId
parameters.description: The ID of the event to retrieve.

parameters.name: eventTypeName
parameters.description: The event type of the event to retrieve.

nested_items.name: eventTimestamp
nested_items.description: The timestamp that defines when the event under evaluation occurred. The timestamp must be specified using ISO 8601 standard in UTC.

nested_items.name: eventVariables
nested_items.description: Names of the event type's variables you defined in Amazon Fraud Detector to represent data elements and their corresponding values for the event you are sending for evaluation.

nested_items.name: currentLabel
nested_items.description: The label associated with the event.

nested_items.name: labelTimestamp
nested_items.description: The timestamp associated with the label to update. The timestamp must be specified using ISO 8601 standard in UTC.

nested_items.name: entityId
nested_items.description: The entity ID. If you do not know the entityId, you can pass unknown, which is areserved string literal.
